where ~pi is the momentum vector of particle i, and ~nT is the thrust axis to be determined. We define o/ j 1 \Gamma T . An axis ~nmaj can be found to maximize the momentum sum transverse to ~nT , and an axis ~nmin is defined to be perpendicular to the two axes ~nT and ~nmaj . The variables thrust-major Tmaj and thrust-minor Tmin are obtained by replacing ~nT in Eq. (5) by ~nmaj or ~nmin, respectively. The oblateness O is then given by [35] O = Tmaj\Gamma Tmin. The C-parameter, C = 3(*1*2+*2*3+*3*1), is derived from the eigenvalues *i (i = 1,2,3) of the infrared-safe momentum tensor [36]:

