FIG. 2. Values of ffs(M 2Z ) from QCD fits to the data using: (a) physical (solid circles), and experimentally-optimised (open circles) scales; (b) PMS- (solid circles), FAC- (solid triangles), and BLM- (open squares) optimised scales. In all cases only experimental error bars are shown. For each observable the shaded region indicates the total uncertainty estimated in Ref. [12], dominated by the contribution from wide variation of the renormalisation scale.

